text.section:
In accordance with the Maryland Constitution and other law, the Governor shall include in each budget bill:
an appropriation to pay the principal of and interest on the State debt;
without revision, the appropriations requested for public schools, as certified by the State Superintendent of Schools;
without revision, the appropriations requested for the Legislative Branch of the State government, as certified by the presiding officers of the General Assembly;
without revision, the appropriations requested for the Judicial Branch of the State government, as certified by the Chief Judge of the Court of Appeals;
the appropriations requested by the Governor for the Executive Branch of the State government;
the appropriations required by law to be included with the appropriations for the Executive Branch;
appropriations for the salaries required by law to be paid by the State; and
any other appropriations required by the Maryland Constitution or other law to be included in the budget bill.
